\subsubsection{\textbf{Feature Concatenation Layer}}
\label{s325}
While the preceding layers learn discriminative features, a single branch may be insufficient. Therefore, this layer concatenates multiple vectors. We observed that as the number of concatenated features increased, the p-value for classification error also increased, which we interpreted as a definitive proof that the model's accuracy was improving.
